ab sapienti uiro: ac sapientia uera of the MSS is retained by Mo. and Kuh. Orelli proposed to cut these words out. Almost all other recent editors adopt Bentley's conj. ab sapienti uiro. Sapi- entia uera is an odd expression and with that reading we should have ab lzz's (or something awkwardly supplied from ab his) carried on to the second clause, whereas ab sapienti uiro gives a natural antithesis to ab lzz‘s. An emendation in the margin of the edition of Lambinus and Gothofredus, ratio uera ac sapientia, may be noticed.
